<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
1.9-2.0 mm long (mean = 1.97 mm; n = 5); 2.71-2.86
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the elytral disc flat with short, steep declivity; posterolateral margin of elytra carinate; declivity with sparse minor denticles, much less abundant than strial punctures; and a pair of slightly larger denticles on interstriae 3.
</paragraph>
